cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.DB 

This paper is primarily focused on improving information retrieval from the World Wide Web, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the development of a system that captures user data to create a personal contextual profile, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and potentially cybersecurity (cs.CY) concerns. The system is designed to improve the search experience for users, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) considerations. Finally, the system involves the creation and sharing of a knowledge base, which could involve database (cs.DB) management techniques.
